      <section name="Quick Start">
        
        <p>
          At this moment Hippo ECM is still in an early development stage. To run it,
          it is necessary to checkout the sources from the SVN repository, and build
          them using Maven. A full guide can be found under 
          <a href="../extend-hippo-ecm/building/maven.html">Building with Maven</a>.
          The short version below is targeted at those who know what they are doing.
        </p>
        
        <subsection name="Checkout the sources">
<source>
~/> svn co https://svn.hippocms.org/repos/hippo/hippo-ecm/trunk hippo-ecm
</source>
        </subsection>          

        <subsection name="Build Hippo ECM">
<source>
~/> cd hippo-ecm
~/hippo-ecm> mvn install
</source>          
        </subsection>          

        <subsection name="Start RMI Registry">
<source>
~/hippo-ecm> $JAVA_HOME/bin/rmiregistry &amp;				
</source>          
        </subsection>          

        <subsection name="Run Hippo ECM">
<source>
~/hippo-ecm> cd application/cms-prototype/repository
~/hippo-ecm/application/cms-prototype/repository> mvn jetty:run-war
</source>          
        <p>
          And in a different console:
        </p>
<source>
~/hippo-ecm> cd application/cms-prototype/frontend
~/hippo-ecm/application/cms-prototype/frontend> mvn jetty:run-war
</source>          
        <p>
          Finally, direct your browser to <a href="http://localhost:8082/">http://localhost:8082</a>.
        </p>
        </subsection>          
        
      </section>
        
        
